# Agent Router — What to Read by Task

Read **only** the specs relevant to your task. Use this table to navigate.

## Task → Spec routing

| Task domain | Spec to read | Key sections |
|-------------|-------------|--------------|
| Road logic, placement, bridges | `.cursor/specs/roads-system.md` + geography spec §9, §10, §13, **§14.5** | Validation surface, resolver rules, stroke / lip / wet run |
| Water, terrain, cliffs, shores | `.cursor/specs/water-terrain-system.md` + geography spec §2–§5, §11–§12 | Height model, layered visuals, lakes, rivers |
| Simulation, AUTO growth | `.cursor/specs/simulation-system.md` | Tick order, AUTO pipeline, **§Rings** (centroid + growth rings) |
| Save / load | `.cursor/specs/persistence-system.md` + geography spec §7.4, §11.5 | Load pipeline, visual restore |
| Manager responsibilities | `.cursor/specs/managers-reference.md` | Responsibilities, dependencies |
| Zones, buildings, RCI | `.cursor/specs/managers-reference.md` — **Zones & Buildings** | Zone lifecycle, pivot, density, undeveloped light zoning |
| Demand, desirability | `.cursor/specs/managers-reference.md` — **Demand (R / C / I)** | DemandManager, CityStats, growth pressure |
| Forests, regional map, utilities | `.cursor/specs/managers-reference.md` — **World features** | ForestManager, RegionalMapManager, resource buildings |
| In-game notifications | `.cursor/specs/managers-reference.md` — **Game notifications** | GameNotificationManager singleton |
| Slopes, sorting, geography | `.cursor/specs/isometric-geography-system.md` §1–§7 | Coordinates, heights, sorting formula |
| UI changes | `.cursor/specs/ui-design-system.md` | Foundations, components |
| Coding standards | `.cursor/rules/coding-conventions.mdc` | XML docs, naming, prefabs |
| Domain terms | `.cursor/specs/glossary.md` | Quick definitions |
| Backlog / issues | `BACKLOG.md` (only if task involves an issue) | — |
| Full dependency map | `ARCHITECTURE.md` | System layers, dep table |

## Canonical geography spec

`.cursor/specs/isometric-geography-system.md` is the **single source of truth** for grid math, heights, slopes, water/shore/cliffs, sorting, terraform, roads, rivers, pathfinding. When another doc disagrees, the geography spec wins.

